# Replay and Observability Rules

## Replay Engine
- Reconstruct sessions from persisted normalized events + config snapshot.
- Replay clock must not depend on wall-clock time except for controlled pacing.
- Must reuse the SAME state, signal, risk, and paper execution code as live paper mode.
- Determinism guarantee: identical inputs + config → identical outputs.
- Replay ordering: recv_mono_ns → ingest_seq → event_id.
- If source timestamps conflict with receive order, preserve recorded ingestion order and report the gap.
- Determinism check mode: compare replay outputs to prior recorded outputs, fail on divergence outside allowed fields.
- Replay must NOT connect to external market data or submit any orders.

## Reports
- Per-market: metadata, signals, paper orders, fills, P&L, skip reasons, risk halts, feed staleness windows, latency.
- Must be readable enough to decide whether the strategy has edge.
- Must work offline without external network access.

## Metrics (Prometheus)
- Feed latency by source, message rate by source, WS reconnect count.
- Book staleness, reference-feed staleness.
- Signal count, paper order/fill counts, paper P&L.
- Risk halt count, replay determinism failures.
- Storage write failures.
- Metrics are NOT the source of record — persisted events + config snapshots are.

## Logging
- Structured tracing with JSON output.
- Every log must include: run_id, mode, and relevant market_id/asset/source/event_type.
- Every simulated order must log a reason: placed, skipped, canceled, filled, or halted.
